{"comments":"Coherence Atoms - model self-consistency primitives.\n\nThese atoms express the degree to which a world-model is internally\nconsistent. When an agent's model contains contradictions, these\nvalues shift to signal that something is wrong.\n\n## Philosophy\nAt billion-agent scale, agents must be able to reason about the\nhealth of their own models. A contradiction detected in reasoning\nshould be expressible as data — not just logged, but typed and\nbounded so it can be composed, compared, and reasoned about.\n\n## Atoms\n```\n| Coherence     | Number | 0.0 | 1.0 | clamps | Model self-consistency   |\n| Contradiction | Number | 0.0 | 1.0 | clamps | Detected contradictions  |\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show, min, max)\n\n## Dependents\n- Epistemic/State.purs (composes into OperationalState)\n- Agent.* (self-monitoring)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[73,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[73,1]},"title":"eqCoherence"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[74,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[74,1]},"title":"ordCoherence"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[77,53],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[76,1]},"title":"showCoherence"}],"comments":"Model coherence (0.0-1.0, clamps).\n\nExpresses how self-consistent the current world-model is.\n0.0 = completely incoherent (contradictions everywhere)\n1.0 = fully coherent (no detected contradictions)\n\nThis is not a binary — partial coherence is meaningful.\nA model can have localized contradictions while remaining\nmostly functional.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[71,37],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[71,1]},"title":"Coherence"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a bounded coherence (clamps to 0.0-1.0)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[88,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[88,1]},"title":"mkCoherence"},{"children":[],"comments":"Unwrap the coherence value\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[92,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[92,1]},"title":"unwrapCoherence"},{"children":[],"comments":"Minimum coherence (0.0 - completely incoherent)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[80,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[80,1]},"title":"minCoherence"},{"children":[],"comments":"Maximum coherence (1.0 - fully coherent)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[84,1]},"title":"maxCoherence"},{"children":[],"comments":"Incoherent state (0.0)\nThe model is in severe contradiction with itself.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[97,24],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[97,1]},"title":"incoherent"},{"children":[],"comments":"Partially coherent (0.5)\nSignificant contradictions exist but model is partially functional.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[102,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[102,1]},"title":"partiallyCoherent"},{"children":[],"comments":"Mostly coherent (0.85)\nMinor inconsistencies, model is largely functional.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Epistemic","Coherence"],"Coherence"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[107,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Epistemic/Coherence.purs","start":[107,1]},"title":"mostlyCoherent"},{"children":[],"comments":"Fully coherent (1.0)\nNo detected contradictio